article.headline: Hartford 59, Stony Brook 44
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. (AP) -- Bo Taylor scored 17 points to lead Hartford to a 59-44 victory over Stony Brook on Sunday. Taylor was the only double-figures scorer for the Hawks (11-15, 5-8 America East), who held a 21-18 halftime lead in route to their second consecutive win after seven straight losses. Mike Popoko's 10 points topped the Sea Wolves (8-16, 3-9), who have lost five of their last six. Popoko boosted his career points total to 1,006, making him the 19th player in school history to go reach one thousand. After Popoko's jumper gave the home team a 14-13 lead, Taylor's layup put the Hawks up for good with 3:06 remaining in the first half. A jumper by Tafo Fabrice finished off a 13-4 run that opened the second half and put Hartford in command 34-22 at 14:00. Two foul shots by Taylor at 7:32 put the game out of reach 49-29.
